article.description: Sophomore Michelle Munoz scored 12 points to lead No. 17 Ohio State to a 67-53 triumph over St. John's in the first round of the Buckeye Classic.
article.headline: Munoz leads Buckeyes with 12 points
article.linkText: No. 17 Ohio State advances to finals of Buckeye Classic
article.story: COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Michelle Munoz scored 12 points to lead Ohio State (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today; No. 18 AP) to a 67-53 victory over St. John's on Saturday in the first round of the Buckeye Classic. Candace Dark added 11 points for Ohio State (6-1), which will face Penn in the championship game Sunday. Penn beat Dayton 90-69. Ohio State led by as many as 17 in the first half, and went into the break with a 31-21 lead. Ohio State shot 53.1 percent from the floor, while the Red Storm shot 32.8 percent. Angie Clark had 15 points and 12 rebounds for St. John's (4-5), and Kim Macmillan scored 12 of her 14 points off 3-pointers.
